BACKUP.Definition: something that you use to replace something else if it is lost or damaged

GENE BANK.Definition: a repository that preserves genetic material

NUCLEAR HOLOCAUST.Definition: an event where a nuclear explosion destroys large parts of an area

AISLE.Definition: a long, narrow space, normally between seats or shelves

INTENTIONS.Definition: things that you want to do

INFESTATION.Definition: a situation where there are too many insects, ants etc

BARRIERS.Definition: obstacle, things that would stop you doing something

TWIST OF FATE.Definition: something that happens by chance, often in an unfortunate or strange way
